## Foundation

The **Fighters Guild** was founded in 2E 321 by the **Akaviri Potentate Versidue-Shaie** as part of his Imperial guild reforms. Created as a legal alternative to unregulated mercenary work, it offered:
- A legal framework for independent fighters
- Verified and guaranteed contracts
- Legal protection for its members
- Shared training and resources

## Structure

### Hierarchy
| Rank | Responsibility |
|------|---------------|
| Guild Master | Supreme direction, appointments |
| Champion | Regional operational command |
| Weaponmaster | Training, evaluation |
| Guardian | Head of a local guild hall |
| Protector | Confirmed members |
| Warrior | Standard members |
| Associate | Recruits |

### Organization
- Guild halls in every major city
- Local autonomy under Imperial charter
- Contracts posted publicly
- Fixed remuneration based on difficulty

## Types of Contracts

The Guild accepts:
- **Extermination** — clearing creatures (rats, trolls, vampires, bandits)
- **Escort** — protecting caravans and travelers
- **Retrieval** — recovering objects lost in dangerous areas
- **Guard duty** — protecting locations or persons
- **Exploration** — clearing ruins, caves, abandoned forts

The Guild **refuses**:
- Assassination
- Intimidation
- Inter-guild combat (except under exceptional circumstances)
- Illegal contracts

## Across the Eras

### Second Era (ESO)
- Very active during the Interregnum
- Corrupted by the necromancer Molag Bal through the Worm Cult
- Reformed by the Vestige
- Power struggle with the Worm Cult

### Third Era
- Present in all Imperial provinces
- In Morrowind: competition with the Great Houses (which have their own warriors)
- In Cyrodiil: main hall in every city
- Growing rivalry with the Dark Brotherhood (which encroaches on the "violence market")

### Fourth Era
- Weakened by the collapse of the Empire
- In Skyrim: replaced by the **Companions** (similar structure but culturally Nordic)
- Survives in other provinces with diminished influence

## Code of Honor

Fundamental rules:
1. Never abandon an accepted contract (except proven immorality)
2. Do not steal from Guild members
3. Do not kill without contractual justification
4. Obey the orders of superiors on a mission
5. Share profits according to the terms of the contract

## Differences with the Companions

| Aspect | Fighters Guild | Companions |
|--------|---------------|------------|
| Structure | Formal hierarchy | Informal |
| Charter | Imperial | None |
| Reach | All of Tamriel | Skyrim only |
| Motivation | Profit | Honor |
| Specialty | General mercenary work | Heroic combat |
| Religion | Secular | Shor / Nordic traditions |

## Rivals and Enemies

- **Dark Brotherhood** — illegal assassins
- **Camonna Tong** — organized crime in Morrowind
- **Bandits** — targets and competitors
- **Worm Cult** (Order of the Black Worm) — necromantic infiltration
